* Able to meet tight deadlines
* Keep calm under pressure
* Have a ‘can do’ attitude
* Have an eye for detail
* Get the best out of smth.
* Focused
* Problem solving skills
* Optimistic 
* Analytical skills
* Able to accept criticism
* Follow instructions
* respectful

**Quotes**
* Whenever you are asked if you can do a job, tell them, ‘Certainly, I can!’ – and get busy finding out how to do it. Theodor Roosevelt

* The difference between a job and a career is the difference between 40 and 60 hours a week. Robert Frost

* The best way to appreciate your job is to imagine yourself without one. Oscar Wilde

* Whatever your life’s work is, do it well. A man should do his job so well that the living, the dead, and the unborn could do it no better. Martin Luther King, Jr.

* Find a job you like and you add five days to every week. Jackson Brown

**Questions**
* Tell me about yourself
* Are you a team player?
* Why should we hire you?
* What irritates you about co-workers?
* What is your strength?
* What kind of person would you refuse to work with?
* Tell me about your ability to work under pressure.
* What motivates you to do your best?
* Do you have any blind spots?
* Are you an ambitious person? In what way?

**Accomplishments**
* Accomplished
* Advised
* Applied
* Approved
* Assisted
* Completed
* Created
* Developed
* Increased
* overcame

* Major accomplishment
* A thirst for knowledge/education/info
* Able to work without supervision
* Able to handle multiple projects simultaneously
* Have short and long-term goals
* Have extensive/robust experience
* Have first-hand experience
* Have rich educational background
* Long range planning

**Questions**
* Tell me about your education background and working experience
* What experience do you have in this field?
* What have you done to improve your knowledge recently?
* Tell me about a problem you had with a supervisor
* What has disappointed you about a job?
* What have you learnt from mistakes on the job?*
* Why did you leave your last job?
* Have you ever been fired?
* What would make you stay at your previous job?
* Are you applying for any other organizations?
* What do you know about this company?
* Why do you want to work with us?
* Why should we hire you?
* How does our company differ from your previous one?
* What was the last project you headed up and what was the outcome?
* Give me an example of a time you went above and beyond the call of duty at work.
* Can you describe a time when your work was criticized?
* Have you ever been on a team where someone was not pulling their own weight? How did you handle it?
* What is your greatest failure and what did you learn from it?
* What irritates you about other people, and how do you deal with it?
* If your supervisor asked you to do smth you disagree with, what would you do?
* How would you handle a situation if you were required to finish multiple tasks by the end of the day and there was no possible way to do that?

**Why our company?**
* Benefit
* Lack of..
